(90, 'Visite', '<u>Montpellier, it''s...</u><br><br><u>The NEWS, Year 2008 in the limelight ...</u><br >'),
(91, 'Visite', '  A  SECOND LINE FOR THE TRAMWAY : From Jacou to Saint-Jean-de-Védas, cross Montpellier from the North-East to the South-West !<br />'),
(92, 'Visite', '  BRAND-NEW MUSEE FABRE REOPENS : Rediscover masterpieces : History of the creation of Europe, from the Renaissance to nowadays, through painting collections and sculptures restored representing significant historical events and related to the history of art<br><u> Exhibition Gustave Courbet (1819-1877)</u> until September 28th, 2008...<br> Retrospective one special on Gustave Courbet, of a historical and unpublished largeness, first  one in France since 1977. Homage has this huge artist, close friend of our city where it stayed lead several times</br> '),
(93, 'Visite', '  AMAZONIAN GREENHOUSE : The Zoo du Lunaret makes you travel and dream ... Discover it from a different point of view since May 2007<br />'),
(94, 'Visite', '  MARE NOSTRUM : a Gigantic Aquarium : submarine landscapes, beaches and lagoons : escape reality and discover a wonderful world ! <br />'),
(95, 'Visite', ''),
(96, 'Visite', ''),
(97, 'Visite', '  Treasures of a Rich Historical and Architectural Heritage : The Place de la Comédie and its Trois Grâces, Louis 14th  standing proudly in front of the Arc de triomphe, in the district of the Peyrou, a green and nice place for a walk in the heart of the city'),
(98, 'Visite', '  Montpellier enjoys Art and Culture very much : Opéra de la Comédie, a majestic stage of lyric art in France'),
(99, 'Visite', '<img src=''/alex/Euromedecine/image/point2.gif'' alt='''' />  Discover its Sacred Places : St-Pierre''s Cathedral, the most ancient university in Western Europe still in place'),
(100, 'Visite', '  Montpellier, a Young and Dynamic City : Cultural Melting-Pot, trendy places : musical bars, theme bars, show halls (Zénit, Corum)'),
(101, 'Visite', '  City by the side of Nature : Jardins des Plantes, Domaine de Méric (Orangery, green spaces with mediterranean scents), Jardins de l''Esplanade, the Rives du Lez (beautiful fountains of water illuminated by night), the Zoo du Lunaret and its 320 animals ! <br/><br><u>Enter in the heart of a charming wild natural world : ...</u><br/>'),
(102, 'Visite', '  Very close to the littoral and its charms :<br/>  Villeneuve-les-Maguelones, Palavas-les-Flots, la Grande Motte, Carnon<br/>Wide and long sandy beaches, sand-hills and reeds in a wonderful endless scenery...Discover also the traditions of Camargue and remarkable landscapes between sea and country and do not forget to contemplate the wide ponds full of pink flamingoes<br/>'),
(103, 'Visite', ''),
(104, 'Visite', ' <img src=''/alex/Euromedecine/image/point2.gif'' alt='''' /> Beautiful Natural Spots : Less than one hour from here !<br/>&#9829;  The Medieval Villages :  St-Guilhem-le-Désert, Les Matelles, Sauges, St-Martin-de-Londres.<br/><br>&#9829;  The Pic St-Loup : discover its well-groomed vineyards whose wines are labelled AOC, signposted footpaths, horse-riding<br/>&#9829;  St-Guilhem-le-Désert : the Gorges de l''Hérault, from Brissac to the Pont du Diable (if translated, it would be : Bridge of Devil)<br/>&#9829;  The Lac du Salagou (Lake of Salagou) <br/>&#9829;  The Cirque de Navacelles<br/>&#9829;  The Grotte des Demoiselles<br/>&#9829;  Cirque and Grotte de Labeil (Cave of Labeil)<br/>&#9829;  The Grotte de la Clamouse<br/>&#9829;  And finally the famous Viaduc de Millau (Viaduct of Millau) <br/><br>Get more information on the following Web Sites : <br/><br><a href="http://www.herault-tourisme.fr"> www.herault-tourisme.fr</a><br /><br><a href="http://www.ot-montpellier.fr"> www.ot-montpellier.fr</a><br /><br>'),
