(115, 39, 'descript', 'La Casa Los Gorriones fue fundada el 5 de marzo de 2002 por Gil y Chantal. Este orfanato acoge a ninos entre 0 y 18 anos de edad en Ayacucho, una de las regiones mas pobres del Peru.'),
(116, 39, 'keyw', 'Ayachucho, Casa, hogar, los, gorriones, ninos, ayudar, dessarollo,Peru, volontario, donacion, construccion,viajar, viaje, padrinos, educacion, orfanato'),
(117, 39, 'body', '<table style="width: 972px; height: 404px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Dayana, El s&iacute;ndrome de Lennox-Gastaut.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p><img style="margin: 2px 5px 0px 2px; float: left;" src="../image/dayana.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="268" /> Dayana naci&ograve; el 17 de febrero del a&ntilde;o 2000, sus convulsiones empezaron cuando ella ten&igrave;a dos meses de nacida, y desde entonces sigue un tratamiento.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Desde julio 2000 hasta marzo 2006 ella estuvo internada en el hospital de Mogrobejo donde los m&egrave;dicos le diagnosticar&oacute;n el sindrome de &ldquo;Lennox Gastaut&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Hoy en d&igrave;a Dayana tiene 9 a&ntilde;os y vive con sus padres y su hermanita en Ayacucho. Ellos viven en una casa muy humilde donde solo cuentan con el servicio de agua y de electricidad.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>El pap&agrave; trabajaba como obrero pero por el efuerso f&igrave;sico realizado en el trabajo se maltrato la espalda y ahora trabaja como conductor de mototaxi, la mam&agrave; solo se dedica a las labores del hogar y a cuidar a Dayana.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>El caso de Dayana brindo a que su familia sea vuelva mas unida y asi poder afrontar los problemas de cada d&igrave;a, pero ellos no cuentan con los recursos necesarios para poder pagar el medicamento &ldquo;el Felbatol&rdquo; que es muy costoso(300 dolares), ya que gracias a este medicamento ella se ha podido mantener sin convulsiones, puede caminar y no se golpea mucho, casi lleva una vida normal. <br /><br /> Entonces estamos buscando a unos padrinos de buen coraz&oacute;n para que puedan asumir los gastos del medicamento de Dayana mensualmente.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Para apoyar Dayana, contacta :&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@gorio.com/alex/Gorriones"><span style="font-size: medium;">donasian_losgorriones@hotmail.com</span></a><span style="font-size: medium;"> o </span><a href="mailto:info@kuska.org"><span style="font-size: medium;">info@kuska.org</span></a></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>'),
(121, 41, 'descript', 'The Casa hogar Los Gorriones is a small family oriented orphanage in the region of Ayacucho in Peru.Los Gorriones welcomes abandoned children from age 0 to 18.'),
(122, 41, 'keyw', 'Casa, hogar, los, gorriones, orphanage, sparrows, children, needs, special, poverty, ayacucho, volunteer, work, programs, donations, help, education, health, care, kuska, construction, house, sponsor, program, food, history,development, international.'),
(123, 41, 'body', '<table style=" width: 972px; " border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<table style="width: 506px; height: 341px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Who are we ?<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p><img style="float: left;margin-bottom:0; margin-left:2px; margin-right:5px; margin-top:2px;" src=" ../image/casa_sommes.jpg " alt="" width="240" height="196" />La casa Los Gorriones was founded on March 5th, 2002 by Gil and Chantal...This orphanage welcomes children aged 0 to 18 in Ayacucho, the poorest region in Peru.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>La Casa Hogar Los Gorriones is registered and recognized by the Peruvan government.&nbsp; We also work in close collaboration with the familly judge, social services and adoption services.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>24 children are currently living at Los Gorriones.&nbsp; Daddy Gil, mommy Chantal and the entire team believe in the importance of recreating a family environment.&nbsp; Love, support and listening are our priorities.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n<td rowspan="2">\r\n<table style="width: 462px; height: 463px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Who are we helping ?<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" style="text-align: justify;">La casa welcomes children aged 0 to 18 who are in need.&nbsp; Many of them have severe physical and mental illness.&nbsp; Other orphanages will not assume responsabilities for children with special needs that require unique services and medications, therefore demanding more time and more expenses. <br />&nbsp;<br />In many cases, the fact that the parents or immediate family have abandoned their child is not recognized.&nbsp; For exemples, the parents do not wish to have their child adopted by a tier party but neither can they afford to care for him.&nbsp; Los Gorriones will then assume the responsability of the child while keeping close link with the family, who can visit la casa as often as they wish to.<br />&nbsp;<br />In other instances, the family Judge recognizes that the child is abandoned.&nbsp; The child is then under the responsability of Los Gorriones and placed on the national adoption list.<br />In the most horrifying cases, the children are simple left to themselves on the street, often under terrible conditions.<br />&nbsp;<br />The majority of children arriving at the orphenage are affected by sever malnutrition, trauma and sickness and bare knowledge of personal hygiene.&nbsp; Direct consequences of the poverty in which they live.<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<table style="width: 506px; height: 119px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Family vision<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p><span>Los Gorriones priority is to offer a family spirit in the orphanage.&nbsp; We promote a family environment based on respect, listening, responsability and solidarity by seeing after each child self-esteem and personality development.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td rowspan="2">\r\n<table style="float: left; width: 506px; height: 438px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Children''s welcoming<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p>The entry of children does not depend of any criteria and preferences. It''s a work coordination between the family court and the parents or member of the family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The social assistance evaluation determines the degree of poverty and abandon of the children.&nbsp; Once the child is accepted, an educational and supporting plan is developted by Los Gorriones, according to his age,and mental and physical health.&nbsp; In the case of a special needs child, necessary mesures are taken with professional aid to give the child all the chances to benefit of a normal life.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The child evolution&nbsp; will benefit from continious evaluations.&nbsp; In the case of a complete abandon of the child by the parents and family, the child''s name will then be place on the national adoption list of the adoption office.&nbsp; Los Gorriones can then anticipate adoption demand.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>These demands are seriously considered by respecting the adoption laws and rules in effect.&nbsp; In coordination with the adoption office, we make sure the process is made in the best interests of the child and that he will continue his normal psychological, academic and social growing process.&nbsp; A following is made after the adoption and all necessary actions would be taken if unfavorable situations occur.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style="height: 224px;" valign="top">\r\n<table style="float: left; width: 462px; height: 224px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Health care<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p><img style="float: left;margin-bottom:0; margin-left:2px; margin-right:5px; margin-top:2px;" src=" ../image/casa_sante.jpg " alt="" />Every child is followed by a professional doctor and receive all health cares needed, physical and psychological.&nbsp; Several children at la casa suffer from severe physical and mental handicaps and are daily stimulated by appropriate exercices.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A good nutrition is crucial to a well development of these kids who had almost all suffer of malnutrition.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>At la casa Los Gorriones, a cook prepares daily three (3) good meals for the whole family!</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<table style="float: left; width: 461px; height: 172px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Education<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p>With the Education Sponsorship Program, each&nbsp; child (physicaly capable of moving) is registered to a private school and receive adequate education.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For physicaly restreined and special needs children, educative activities and support are given at the orphenage by professionals with the help of volunteers and the team of Los Gorriones.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>'),
(124, 42, 'descript', ''),
(125, 42, 'keyw', ''),
(126, 42, 'body', ''),
(127, 43, 'descript', 'The Casa hogar Los Gorriones is a small family oriented orphanage in the region of Ayacucho in Peru.Los Gorriones welcomes abandoned children from age 0 to 18.'),
(128, 43, 'keyw', 'Casa, hogar, los, gorriones, orphanage, sparrows, children, needs, special, poverty, ayacucho, volunteer, work, programs, donations, help, education, health, care, kuska, construction, house, sponsor, program, food, history,development, international.');
INSERT INTO `gor_lang_pages` (`id_pages`, `id_menus`, `title`, `contain`) VALUES
(129, 43, 'body', '<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Margary 10/01/1994<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Margary.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="113" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">Margary&rsquo;s oldest sister, guardian of her 4 younger brothers and sisters, brought her sister to the house. Their parents were alcoholics and both died one quickly after the other. Margary&rsquo;s brothers also live in orphanages. Before coming to the house, Margary had never left her parents&rsquo; house and she had never been to school. She never experienced her parents&rsquo; love and they didn&rsquo;t bring her up. Margary is mentally handicapped and she has trouble speaking. At first, nobody could understand what she said and she was very frightened of men. She used to hide her toys because she didn&rsquo;t know how to play with them. Now she goes to school with Sabina. Margary is always cheerful, she laughs a lot and likes playing with the younger children and the volunteers. She helps a lot in the cuarto de Lupes. Sometimes she doesn&rsquo;t know when to stop teasing, because she doesn&rsquo;t know the boundaries between acceptable and unacceptable behaviour. She liked dancing, volleyball, and she is very energetic.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">No&eacute;mi 14/12/2004<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/noemi.jpg" alt="" width="112" height="150" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">No&eacute;mie (or Mimi) came to the house with chronic malnutrition. She was hardly able to walk properly. Her mother had lost her whole family during the period of terrorism in the region and had grown up with adoptive parents. Seriously traumatized, Mimi&rsquo;s mother used to live on the streets more than at home. At 15 she became pregnant &ndash; Mimi&rsquo;s older sister lives in another home. Now her mother has had a third child and Mimi lives in the house. Working with Mimi calls for a lot of patience, but she is delightful. You have to watch out because the other children reject her. Her smile is precious. She loves learning new things, and likes adult attention. She loves it when volunteers that she knows well help her get dressed. She also loves jigsaw puzzles; drawing ... she needs to be stimulated to work on her balance. More than most, Mimi is a cheerful child.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Favio 17/12/1996<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Favio.jpg" alt="" width="82" height="113" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">(Brother of Sergio, Luis, Abel, and Brenda)<br />Just like his friend Emerson, he also enjoys playing football and riding his bike. Favio is a straightforward child, sometimes a bit shy with other people and likes adult contact.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Luis 14/04/1998<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Luis.jpg" alt="" width="98" height="112" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">(Brother of Sergio, Favio, Abel, and Brenda)<br />Like the other boys, he also loves playing football and riding his bike, and he does it well. Luis is a very active and alert boy. He wants to be good at everything, and if anyone says he&rsquo;s done something badly he can really moan. He often fights with his brother Abel.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Abel 21/02/2000<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Abel.jpg" alt="" width="98" height="125" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">(Brother of Sergio, Luis, Favio, and Brenda)<br />Abel also likes playing football, but he also often plays with the younger children. He is best friends with Ferm&iacute;n and his little brother Sergio. He can be very nice and kind, but he can also sometimes be difficult. He used to often lie and steal books from the house ... to sell them at school. A smart child! Sometimes he teases the younger children, like Alonso, and makes them cry. When there is a meeting he always behaves like a very understanding boy, and apologizes for the upset he has caused himself and the other children, but the question is does his behaviour ever really change?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Brenda 17/07/2003<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Brenda.jpg" alt="" width="95" height="118" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">(Sister of Sergio, Abel, Favio and Luis)<br />She is the little princess of the house. She likes attention and loves to dance. Her best friend is Deyse, and the two girls are always together. Now they need to learn how to do things on their own. Brenda likes playing all sorts of games with the volunteers, she&rsquo;s very pretty and cheerful child. She can also be very proud.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Sergio 18/06/2004<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Sergio1.jpg" alt="" width="97" height="109" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">(Brother of Favio, Luis, Abel, and Brenda)<br />Sergio is a very cheerful child, with a beautiful smile. At first, he likes to test new volunteers. He asks lots of questions and likes looking at photos of things people in the house have done. He loves sleeping and often cries when he has to get up. The best solution is to wake him up very gently and quietly. He likes playing with the volunteers. Sergio is the most dominant and receptive of the little boys.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Emerson 08/04/1997<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/emerson.jpg" alt="" width="101" height="108" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">In 2002, he arrived at the house with his two older brothers. Their mother had died and two months later their father was arrested for possession of cocaine. He was accused of drug-trafficking and was sent to prison. The brothers came from the jungle where education is very poor. Most children stay at home to help their parents with work. The children regularly visited their father in prison. It was very important that they kept in touch with him. Now, Juan Carlos and Elmer live at URPI, the state-run orphanage for boys aged 6-18; Emerson chose to stay at the house. Now their father is free and lives in the jungle. The brothers will prorably go and live with him again. Emerson is one of the oldest boys in the house. He likes playing football, riding his bike, and playing in the garden. He is often the winner of games and competitions. He&rsquo;s an easy and cheerful child.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Alberto 26/05/2001<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Alberto.jpg" alt="" width="86" height="100" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">Alberto was born in prison, where his parents are doing time for drug-trafficking. He lived there for 2 years until there was an accident and Alberto fell into a pot of boiling water. He was immediately taken to hospital, where he was treated for burns for a month. After that he was supposed to return to the prison, but he refused. Even today, Alberto sometimes still seems to be suffering from shock. His sister Ciliana came to the house 3 years after Alberto. He likes playing with his cars and toys, and he loves animals. He is also best friends with Ferm&iacute;n. Alberto is a kind boy, especially towards Gil and Chantal, but he can also be very difficult. Sometimes there are outbursts, he screams, cries, hits out ... Alberto needs lots of compliments and love.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Ciliana est la petite soeur d''Alberto<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Ciliana.jpg" alt="" width="92" height="122" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">She is a calm and responsible girl. She does all her homework without complaining. Sometimes she can be a bit difficult, if she feels badly treated. She likes playing with the volunteers and she is very creative.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Deysie 16/02/2002<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Deysse.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="93" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">(She is Freddy&rsquo;s sister.) Their mother died from an illness, because she didn&rsquo;t have enough money for medicine, and their father couldn&rsquo;t bring them up on his own and work at the same time. Their grandmother loves them very much and comes to visit them every week. Unfortunately she is also unable to look after them as she already has other small children of her own. Thier father visits them every fortnight and he hopes he&rsquo;ll be able to take them home when they are older. Deysie is a responsible, nice and calm little girl. She looks after her brother Freddy well. She likes playing with her friend Brenda and with the volunteers. However, when she&rsquo;s not happy about something, she makes it very clear!</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Freddy 14/05/2004<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/freddy.jpg" alt="" width="98" height="131" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">Freddy and his sister (Deysie) arrived at the house in 2006 because their mother had died and their father couldn&rsquo;t work and look after them at the same time. Their grandmother loves them very much and comes to visit them often but she can&rsquo;t look after them either has she has her own young children. Their father comes twice a month and hopes that when they are older they&rsquo;ll be able to go and live with him. Working with Freddy requires a lot of patience. He doesn&rsquo;t like sharing his toys, and when another child is playing too, Freddy always wants the other&rsquo;s toy. He often cries for nothing, and the best thing is to leave him to calm down on his own, or to make him laugh by doing something completely different, because if you&rsquo;re too strict, that just makes him cry more. When he&rsquo;s in a good mood, he plays nicely. He&rsquo;s very empathic and always asks how you are. He loves cuddles.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Sabina 16/10/1987<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Sabina.jpg" alt="" width="89" height="100" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">Sabina is 22, and she is the oldest girl in the house. She is hard of hearing and has a mild mental handicap. We don&rsquo;t know much about her past. She was found on the streets of Lima when she was 10. Then she was employed as a cleaner in a house and was often very badly treated. 4 years later she was ended up at the family court because the woman Sabina worked for wanted to move house and couldn&rsquo;t emply her anymore. She came to Ayacucho and to the house. In the mornings Sabina goes to a special school and in the afternoons she helps at the house. She has started to speak a little bit. Sabina is a responsible girl, calm, and very nice. She helps the lupes a lot and in the kitchen. She gets on very well with Francine and she helps her makes cakes. Sabina likes knitting. She&rsquo;ll probably always stay at the house as this has now become her home.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Eberson 16/05/2003</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/eberson4.jpg" alt="" width="84" height="113" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">Eberson arrived at the house in August 2004. Unfortunately he has no family. His mother died when he was born and Eberson was taken in by another family with 6 children. His adoptive mother then died and then he was brought to the house. Eberson is blind and has a cerebral palsy. He goes for therapy 3 times a week. They help him to walk a bit, and are hoping that he&rsquo;ll be able to do this on his own soon. He needs a lot of love and attention. He very affectionate and smiles a lot, but sometimes he can be very aggressive, and when he&rsquo;s not happy, he bangs his head on the floor. He loves playing with a ball and can spend hours listening to music and loves being taken for walks by volunteers, in a manta on their backs. He is on the adoption list.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Sonia 28/11/1993<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/sonia.jpg" alt="" width="126" height="93" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">After Sonia, she is the next oldest girl in the house. She is a responsible girl who helps her brothers and sister and the other children. She is calm and doesn&rsquo;t ask much of the volunteers. You need to take time to get to know her better, to find that she is very lovely girl!</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Florinda 18/02/1993<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Florinda.jpg" alt="" width="111" height="148" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">She is younger than her sister. She can be in a very good mood one day, and then in a very bad mood the next. When she doesn&rsquo;t want to do something, it&rsquo;s very hard to motivate her. On the other hand, when she&rsquo;s in a good mood, she laughs a lot, likes being with the volunteers and playing with the other children.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Jolver 18/09/1998<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Julver.jpg" alt="" width="84" height="100" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">Another boy who likes playing football and riding his bike. He also likes helping in the kitchen. He&rsquo;s a very proud and strong-headed child, and he&rsquo;s not good at apologising if he misbehaves. On the other hand, if you compliment him, he&rsquo;s the happiest boy in the house! He can annoy his brother Alonso to the point of making him cry.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Luis Alonzo or Luighi 27/07/2001<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Luigi.jpg" alt="" width="139" height="103" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">Luis Alonso can be a very nice child, but at the same time, he can be the most difficult child in the house. He often cries and if you get angry with him, he can get really upset, crying, sreaming, hitting ... He often doesn&rsquo;t listen to the volunteers or obey them. But sometimes he&rsquo;ll take your hand and ask you to play with him. He likes playing with his car and in the garden.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Fermin 16/11/1999<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Fermin.jpg" alt="" width="111" height="148" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">Fermin arrived at the house in April 2007 when he was 8. He&rsquo;s a very special child; even though he&rsquo;s 8 years old, he has a mental age of 3. He is mentally handicapped, caused by violence, but his parents are also mentally handicapped. During the first 6 years of his life, Fermin lived with his mother. However, according to his aunt, his mother didn&rsquo;t know what to do with him and locked him in a room for 6 years, depriving him of clothes and food. Fermin was found one cold and rainy day in a corner of a dark lane, he was very dirty, just wearing a jumper, bare feet, and seriously malnourished. He&rsquo;d been so hungry that he&rsquo;d even eaten his own excrement. Working with Fermin demands a lot of concentration and patience. Lots of things that Fermin does don&rsquo;t seem to make any sense. When he arrived at the house, Fermin was hyperactive, used to bite and hit others sometimes ... He regularly ignored what people said to him. But as we didn&rsquo;t know his level of mental handicap, it was difficult to know how much his behaviour was the result of his &lsquo;illness&rsquo; or of the violence he suffered when he was little. Twice a week Fermin goes for therapy. In November 2007, two volunteers created a treatment plan for Fermin, with activities to stimulate him and to help control his aggressive attitude. The work they have done shows that Fermin is capable of understanding and doing things asked of him. It is important for his development that this work with him follows a strict routine, and he will get used to doing basic activities in normal daily life - washing his hands, brushing his teeth, getting dressed, etc. It&rsquo;s also important to treat Fermin like a normal child, and for him to mix as much as possible with the other children. You have to be careful as others might hit him. Fermin loves kisses, looking people in the eye, little bits of paper, water and merry-go-rounds.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Cristofer 17/03/2006<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/christofer2.jpg" alt="" width="140" height="104" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">Cristofer is the youngest child in the house at the moment. He came in August 2007, transferred from another orphenage where they couldn&rsquo;t cope with his psychomotor instability. His mother, who suffers from mental illness, gave birth on a dance floor at a discotheque. Cristofer came into the world smashing his right side straight onto the floor. Now he does daily exercises, physical therapy to stimulate his arms and legs, especially his right hand that he still never uses. Not long ago he said his first word: GRACIAS and has managed to walk 4 steps and is beginning to walk on his own. He&rsquo;s an alert child, a happy baby, with a strong character. He will return to the other orphenage once he&rsquo;s completed the therapy at the house.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Diego 08/12/1999<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Diego.jpg" alt="" width="113" height="102" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">He used to live in the mountains with his mother who went off to work everyday, and so he stayed in the house on his own. His father doesn&rsquo;t have any money or a house. Early on in his life, Diego wasn&rsquo;t stimulated by his surroundings. His mother comes to visit every 2 months, but it&rsquo;s unlikely that Diego will return to live with her. He&rsquo;s the gentlest child in the house. When he doesn&rsquo;t like something, he makes it clear by making little noises. When he came to the house, he couldn&rsquo;t open his eyes, now he can. He manages to make out shadows, but doesn&rsquo;t speak. Diego needs a lot of stimulation as he has cerebral palsy.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Yacner 23/03/2002<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Yackner.jpg" alt="" width="96" height="100" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">Cristofer is the youngest child in the house at the moment. He came in August 2007, transferred from another orphenage where they couldn&rsquo;t cope with his psychomotor instability. His mother, who suffers from mental illness, gave birth on a dance floor at a discotheque. Cristofer came into the world smashing his right side straight onto the floor. Now he does daily exercises, physical therapy to stimulate his arms and legs, especially his right hand that he still never uses. Not long ago he said his first word: GRACIAS and has managed to walk 4 steps and is beginning to walk on his own. He&rsquo;s an alert child, a happy baby, with a strong character. He will return to the other orphenage once he&rsquo;s completed the therapy at the house.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Sheyla 08/04/2003</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Sheila.jpg" alt="" width="91" height="122" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">Sheyla has mild cerebral palsy, and she has problems speaking. Her dislocated hip makes it difficult to walk. She had an operation to try to solve the problem and she can walk on her own now but not without problems. What&rsquo;s more, Sheyla is epileptic. Her mother is young and an alcoholic; she&rsquo;s currently looking for work and needs to sort out her life style. She comes to see her daughter every Sunday and Sheyla sometimes goes to her house too. Sheyla will return to live with her mother one day. Sheyla lacks self-confidence and always needs lots of attention.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Nilda 17/09/2004<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/web3.jpg" alt="" width="141" height="106" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">Nilda arrived in 2005 straight from the hospital where she was born, as she had a serious lung problem, which according to the doctors should have been fatal. She has cerebral palsy and a lung problem. Her father can&rsquo;t read or write and is an alcoholic. She also has 8 brothers. Her mother works out in the countryside in order to be able to bring her family a bit of food. Since her birth, Nilda spent more time in hospital than with her family, but she wasn&rsquo;t welcome at the hospital because the doctors thought she was a hopeless case. Their advice was to leave her to die. But thanks to her time in the house, she has pulled through. She manages to make out shadows. She often has a high temperature, weighs less than average for her age, and her lungs regularly fill up with water. We don&rsquo;t know how long she will survive, but in the meantime she enchants every helper and volunteer with her magnificent smile. She&rsquo;s a little one with lots of goodwill who&rsquo;s fighting for her life.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Ruth Karina 05/03/1999<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/Ruth.jpg" alt="" width="146" height="111" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">Ruth Karina was one of the first 3 children to come to the house. She was found near the rubbish bins, dogs, pigs, and rats. She was taken to the hospital immediately; her malnutrition was very severe and the doctors thought Ruth Karina had cerebral palsy. She couldn&rsquo;t move any part of her body, she couldn&rsquo;t speak, had convulsions (the slightest noise triggered a convulsion), and her body was covered in burns and she was blind. We don&rsquo;t know anything about Ruth Karina&rsquo;s life before she was brought to the house and she&rsquo;ll never be able to tell us. When she came to the house she seemed very sad ... she was in a terrible state for weeks. Gil and Chantal had never seen such an unhappy child, and then one day she smiled. According to the doctors, Ruth Karina&rsquo;s state is irreversible. She can only eat food in liquid form, and feeding her requires a lot of patience.<br /><strong>On 31 December 2003, Ruth Karina was adopted by Gil and Chantal.</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Luis Angel Moreno Casta&ntilde;eda 14/11/2004</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle">&nbsp;<img src="../image/Enfants/nuevoluis.jpg" alt="" width="111" height="175" /></td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">\r\n<p>Luis has a very fragile health. He has the bronchus in very poor condition and has a severe infection in one ear.</p>\r\n<p>In fact he has this infection since he was eight months and it was never treated.</p>\r\n<p>He may need surgery. Luis will be soon enrolled in a private school. He is very happy he doens''t want to go back to his house. Sometimes his mother comes to visit him with this brothers and sisters.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Maria Jesus 28/03/2002</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle"><img src=" ../image/maria jesus web.jpg " alt="" />&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">\r\n<p>&nbsp;The mother of Maria Jesus was abandoned by her husband and lived in extreme poverty. Maria Jes&uacute;s has 2 sisters and a brother. <br />The mother has abandoned her children for + -4 months to reconcile with the father of her youngest child. Almost every child has a different father.<br />Maria Jesus felt from the "manta" of her mother when she was a baby, she left eye use and was diminished.<br />She never left her house, nobody looked after her, she didn''t receive medical treatment because his mother could not afford to offer a follow-up to her daughter.<br />Today Jesus Maria is suffering from a serious handicap.<br />We decided to take care of Maria Jesus to save her from certain death.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 183px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Maria&nbsp;Antonieta 23/08/2001</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text">\r\n<table style="width: 956px; height: 136px;" border="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_children_img" style="width: 160px;" align="center" valign="middle"><img src=" ../image/maria antonieta web.jpg " alt="" />&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="cell_children_text" style="text-align:justify;">The mother is 43 years old and the Maria''s father is 63 years old.<br />Maria Antonieta is borned from the second marriage of the father, he has a first son who is 17 years old, from his first marriage.<br />The family lived in extreme poverty.<br />Maria has a cerebral palsy, she doesn''t walk, doesn''t talk, is almost blind but she is fighting for one day she might be a little more independent.<br />She has received no treatment for his illness.<br />Through rehabilitation, she is learning to walk and to talk.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</p>'),
(130, 44, 'descript', 'The Casa hogar Los Gorriones is a small family oriented orphanage in the region of Ayacucho in Peru.Los Gorriones welcomes abandoned children from age 0 to 18.'),
(131, 44, 'keyw', 'Casa, hogar, los, gorriones, orphanage, sparrows, children, needs, special, poverty, ayacucho, volunteer, work, programs, donations, help, education, health, care, kuska, construction, house, sponsor, program, food, history,development, international.'),
(132, 44, 'body', '<table style="width: 972px; height: 691px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Construction of a new center</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p>The Casa Hogar Los Gorriones is overwhelmed by a growing number of children who are in need of help. Currently the home is forced to&nbsp;turn away many children.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Therefore, Gil has continued for the&nbsp;past few years to try and achieve the objective of taking in as many children as possible.&nbsp;He and his wife have purchased&nbsp;a new plot of land close to the current home which is larger and offers the possibility of taking in more children and also having areas where therapy and study can take place. The main objective with the implementation of this project is to immediately help a lot of children that the house can not currently aid due to lack of infrastructure, but also to help local families seeking support, education, psychological and medical help.</p>\r\n<p><img style="margin: 2px 5px 0px 2px; float: left;" src="../general/file/Projet_construct_plans/Projet_construct_img_1.jpg" alt="" width="339" height="216" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The "Casa Hogar Hogar Los Gorriones" has therefore appealed to a talented architect, Jos&egrave; Whittembury,&nbsp;has kindly&nbsp;made drawings of the new center. He was careful to present a design consistent with the natural elements of Ayacucho and to create a warm and pleasant home for all, in other words, the aim was to respect the well being of the&nbsp;children while preserving the nature and building an infrastructure with local materials.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;The new center can accommodate over 50 children and volunteers. It includes two pavilions, each can hold 25 children, three houses reserved for the founder and his son, volunteers and a couple who will live in one of the&nbsp;two houses. There are&nbsp;also offices for administrators, a rehabilitation center and a library&nbsp;will also be available for children at the center and for local families. There will also be an audiovisual center that will show films every Friday and Saturday for the children in the casa and the children from the surrounding area.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It is important to emphasize that the center was designed with with the handicapped children in mind. This will also help the effectiveness of volunteers. We agreed that the new home will provide a more suitable place for the children to live and encourage people to come and visit us to see what .is going on or to help in any way they can.</p>\r\n<p><img style="margin: 2px 5px 0px 5px; float: right;" src="../general/file/Projet_construct_plans/Projet_construct_img_5.jpg" alt="" width="339" height="203" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The total project is valued at half a million dollars which we are far from acheiving. It is therefore important to quickly acquire the grants needed to begin construction. Once the project is complete we will undoubtedly see a brighter future for the children.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 541px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">The components of the new center</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">The center is inhabited and managed by different teams:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; Fifty children can occupy the available space.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; A team of 20 employees working solely with children.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; A team of 6 employees responsible for maintenance, cleaning and cooking.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; A team of 4 employees responsible for the administration of the home.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; A team of 30 volunteers accompanying the children every day .</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style="margin: 2px 5px 0px 2px; float: left;" src="../general/file/Projet_construct_plans/Projet_construct_img_2.jpg" alt="" width="339" height="203" /></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">The major components of the center will be:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>&bull; Library:</strong> It will be open to all. Our vision is create a place where children from all over the area can come to read, learn and complete their homework. There will also be organized exhibits and public readings.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>&bull; A rehabilitation center:</strong> It&nbsp;will be&nbsp;designed to accommodate children within the center but also children from outside&nbsp;the center&nbsp;and local families will have free access to the center to receive care, medication and counseling. Child care&nbsp;will be&nbsp;administered by a general practitioner, who has been the doctor of the&nbsp;Casa Hogar for several years.</p>\r\n<p>Employees working with children have also learned to master the techniques of massage and relaxation, the rehabilitation center will allow them to practice their skills more easily.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>&bull; An audiovisual center:</strong> Every Friday and Saturday children from the casa and surrounding area will be able to watch a film. We will generally try to show films involving the culture of Peru so that the children can learn about their heritage.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Who benefits from the center?</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Everyone from the surrounding area will benefit, from the children in the Casa, to the those of the surrounding area and also the parents looking for specific help in certain areas.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 407px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Budget estimates for the contruction of the new center</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" align="center"><img src="../image/budget_en.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="535" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 133px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Additional information</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" align="center">\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; text-align: left;">We are motived&nbsp;to see&nbsp;this project through to fruition. We now have nearly a quarter of the total budget and&nbsp;our desire is to start construction as soon as possible. (Gil&nbsp;envisions that construction&nbsp;will begin&nbsp;sometime in&nbsp;2015).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">We depend on your support and generosity. For more information&nbsp;or to make a donation please contact the&nbsp;Los Gorriones office&nbsp;at <a href="mailto:donasian_losgorriones@hotmail.com">donasian_losgorriones@hotmail.com</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">To look at the plans and all the images&nbsp;: <a href="../general/file/Projet_construct_plans.rar">Building Projects</a><br />For a complete description of the center : <a href="../general/file/Projet_construct_memo_en.doc">Description</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</p>'),
(133, 45, 'descript', 'The Casa hogar Los Gorriones is a small family oriented orphanage in the region of Ayacucho in Peru.Los Gorriones welcomes abandoned children from age 0 to 18.'),
(134, 45, 'keyw', 'Casa, hogar, los, gorriones, orphanage, sparrows, children, needs, special, poverty, ayacucho, volunteer, work, programs, donations, help, education, health, care, kuska, construction, house, sponsor, program, food, history,development, international.'),
(135, 45, 'body', '<table style="width: 972px; height: 235px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Description&nbsp;of the&nbsp;project "Cuy"&nbsp;and "Tara"<br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p>The mission is to help eradicate&nbsp;some of the&nbsp;poverty here in Ayacucho, The Casa Hogar Los Gorriones, home for the most disadvantaged children, has developed a new project in the region of Huamanga (around Ayacucho) to address the problem at it`s source. This consists&nbsp;of educating families and providing them with the materials in order to breed and sell guinea pigs including marketing skills. Guinea pigs are a valuable source of food in Peru and could be one of the ways in which many families can dig their way out of poverty.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This will increase their standard of living, food self-sufficiency and will enable them to keep their families together. Moreover, the goal is to empower families by allowing them to repay money for their training by making them take part&nbsp;of the&nbsp;project management. The project is being developed to provide resources for the families and they will also beable to self finance from that point onwards.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It is hoped that these families&nbsp;will also in the future be able to finance other families to do the same.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For a complete and detailed&nbsp;description of the project, download the following document:&nbsp;<a title="Projet des Cuy fran&ccedil;ais" href="../general/file/Projet_cuy_fr.doc">Projet des Cuy fran&ccedil;ais.doc</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 284px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">The guinea pig</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p><img style="float: left;" src=" ../image/casa_cuy.gif " alt="" width="187" height="116" /></p>\r\n<p>The project is closely related to the market. We know that in the city of Ayacucho, 78% of households consume 2.2 guinea pigs per month.</p>\r\n<p>Taking into account families who raise their own guinea pigs, supply&nbsp;for the region of Ayacucho is&nbsp;3,789 guinea pigs per month. If we add to this supply to nearby regions, total&nbsp;rises to 5,389 guinea pigs per month. Demand is currently way outstripping supply.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The meat of guinea pig is recognized as one of the most nutritious in Peru. Furthermore, scientists are currently trying to prove that the meat contains properties which can help prevent cancer. If the investigations prove there are some cancer preventing properties, the international opportunities for exporting guinea pigs could be significant.&nbsp;The&nbsp;gestation period of guinea pigs is relatively short so large numbers can be bred in a relatively short space of time.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Finally, time spent on the care and maintenance of the animals&nbsp;will not exceed one and a half hours each day with the production capacity allocated to each family for the project.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The family undertake other methods of producing income during the rest of the day.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 260px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">The tare</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p><img style="float:left; margin-bottom:0; margin-left:2px; margin-right:5px; margin-top:2px;" src=" ../image/casa_cuy_tara.jpg " alt="" width="186" height="139" />Is a plant that grows in areas between 1,000 and 2,900 meters. It is an interesting export of Peru as it is used for several different things such as tannic acid, used widely in the pelt industry and&nbsp;for pharmaceutical and chemical industries (paint) among others.</p>\r\n<p><br />Global exports of &ldquo;TARRA" are booming.</p>\r\n<p>The 5 largest exporters&nbsp;in Peru demonstrated through figures listed in Annex 1., IDESI Ayacucho know these businesses and maintain relationships with them that will open up tremendous business opportunities for producers becoming involved in the project.</p>\r\n<p><br />Tare is considered as a great&nbsp;plus in the project. Its production requires no work except a minimal knowledge on the seasonality of crops and marketing opportunities.<br />It is a very profitable investment in the long term for families (see table below). The first harvests only occur after a year and half but thereafter the amount collected increases each year. After 10 years the amount will double.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</p>\r\n<table style="width: 972px; height: 186px;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_title">Objectives and impacts</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="cell_text" style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p>*Create 10 new permanent jobs and and therefor a significant increase in living standards of families involved in the project&nbsp;in the long term.</p>\r\n<p>* Make these families autonomous by developing their knowledge and skills.</p>\r\n<p>* Obtain a minimum production of 123 guinea pigs per family at the end of the project.<br />* Plant a maximum tare crop&nbsp;for the land owned by families.</p>\r\n<p>* Allow a self-financing project to extend to other families every three years, and without new appeals for funds.<br />* Improve and upgrade the status of women in poor neighborhoods, who are often abandoned by their husbands and left to look after their many children alone.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>'),
